---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us | RecycleOldTech - Electronics Recycling Directory" 
  description="Learn how RecycleOldTech connects you with certified electronics recycling centers nationwide – our mission, process, and impact."
>
  <!-- Hero Section with Background Image -->
  <div class="relative pt-32 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img src="/images/better-tomorrow.jpg" alt="Environmental sustainability" class="w-full h-full object-cover">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-900/90 via-green-800/85 to-green-700/90"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
        <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-green-200/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-6">
          <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-green-100" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-white text-center">Our Mission</h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xl text-green-50 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Connecting people with certified electronics recycling centers to protect our environment and promote responsible e-waste disposal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <section class="mb-16">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8.228 9c.549-1.165 2.03-2 3.772-2 2.21 0 4 1.343 4 3 0 1.4-1.278 2.575-3.006 2.907-.542.104-.994.54-.994 1.093m0 3h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900">Why We Exist</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-8">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-green-500">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Accessibility</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Making electronics recycling accessible to everyone through our comprehensive directory.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-blue-500">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.031 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Environmental Protection</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Preventing millions of tons of electronic waste from ending up in landfills.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-purple-500">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quality Standards</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Ensuring all recycling centers meet environmental and safety standards.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
            RecycleOldTech was founded with a simple yet crucial mission. We aim to make electronics recycling accessible to everyone. In today's world, electronic devices are increasingly integral to our daily lives. Proper disposal of outdated or broken electronics has never been more important.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Every year, millions of tons of electronic waste end up in landfills. This releases harmful toxins into our environment. We believe that by making it easier to find certified recycling centers, we can help reduce this environmental impact. Our goal is to promote responsible e-waste management across the United States.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Electronics Lifecycle Challenge</h2>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Modern Consumer Patterns</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              The rapid pace of technological advancement has created unprecedented challenges in electronics disposal. Consumer behavior patterns show that people replace devices more frequently than ever before. Smartphones are typically replaced every 2-3 years. Laptops and computers have an average lifespan of 4-5 years. This constant upgrade cycle generates massive amounts of electronic waste.
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Replacement Frequency</h4>
                <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                  <li>• Smartphones: Every 2-3 years</li>
                  <li>• Tablets: Every 3-4 years</li>
                  <li>• Laptops: Every 4-5 years</li>
                  <li>• Desktop computers: Every 5-6 years</li>
                  <li>• Televisions: Every 7-10 years</li>
                  <li>• Gaming consoles: Every 6-8 years</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Disposal Challenges</h4>
                <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                  <li>• Complex material composition</li>
                  <li>• Miniaturization makes separation difficult</li>
                  <li>• Hazardous substances require special handling</li>
                  <li>• Limited consumer awareness of proper disposal</li>
                  <li>• Inconvenient recycling locations</li>
                  <li>• Data security concerns</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Visual break with e-waste problem image -->
        <div class="relative mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <img src="/images/waste.avif" alt="Electronic waste environmental impact" class="w-full h-64 object-cover">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-900/80 to-orange-900/60 flex items-center">
            <div class="px-8">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The E-Waste Crisis</h3>
              <p class="text-red-100">Electronic waste is the fastest-growing waste stream globally.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <section class="mb-16">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900">The Growing E-Waste Problem</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4">Alarming Statistics</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">Global Impact</h4>
                <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                  <li>• 54 million tons of e-waste generated globally each year</li>
                  <li>• Only 20% of e-waste is properly recycled worldwide</li>
                  <li>• E-waste is the fastest-growing waste stream</li>
                  <li>• Contains over 1,000 different toxic substances</li>
                  <li>• Expected to reach 74 million tons by 2030</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">US Specific Data</h4>
                <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                  <li>• 6.9 billion pounds of e-waste generated annually</li>
                  <li>• Average American discards 44 pounds of e-waste yearly</li>
                  <li>• Only 25% of e-waste is recycled in the US</li>
                  <li>• $60 billion worth of raw materials wasted</li>
                  <li>• 9.4 million tons could be diverted from landfills</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
            The exponential growth of electronic waste poses a significant threat to our environment. Toxic materials like lead, mercury, cadmium, and brominated flame retardants leak into soil and groundwater. This contamination affects local ecosystems and human health. The situation requires immediate action from individuals, businesses, and governments.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-3">Health and Environmental Consequences</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Improper e-waste disposal has far-reaching consequences beyond environmental damage:</p>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>• Neurological damage from lead exposure</li>
              <li>• Respiratory problems from toxic fume inhalation</li>
              <li>• Birth defects in communities near disposal sites</li>
              <li>• Contaminated water supplies affecting millions</li>
              <li>• Soil degradation making agriculture impossible</li>
              <li>• Wildlife population decline and ecosystem disruption</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Visual break with recycling solution image -->
        <div class="relative mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
